# AI Content Generation Standards (OpenRouter)

This project uses OpenRouter for all AI-powered content generation, including product titles, descriptions, SEO metadata, and any other content needs. Follow these standards for all AI content generation logic and integration.

## General Principles
- Use [OpenRouter](mdc:https:/openrouter.ai) as the exclusive provider for all AI content generation.
- All OpenRouter integration must be production-grade, modular, and secure from the start.
- **The system must remain 100% free—only use free models from OpenRouter. Paid models are strictly forbidden.**
- Always select the 5 best free models for each content generation task, based on context window, throughput, features (structured outputs, tool calling, etc.), and up-to-date availability. Re-check [OpenRouter's free model listings](mdc:https:/openrouter.ai/models/?max_price=0&fmt=cards) regularly.
- Document and expose all available free models and their capabilities in the codebase and documentation.
- Use advanced OpenRouter features where relevant:
  - [Model Routing](mdc:https:/openrouter.ai/docs/features/model-routing)
  - [Provider Routing](mdc:https:/openrouter.ai/docs/features/provider-routing)
  - [Prompt Caching](mdc:https:/openrouter.ai/docs/features/prompt-caching)
  - [Structured Outputs](mdc:https:/openrouter.ai/docs/features/structured-outputs)
  - [Tool Calling](mdc:https:/openrouter.ai/docs/features/tool-calling)
  - [Message Transforms](mdc:https:/openrouter.ai/docs/features/message-transforms)
  - [Uptime Optimization](mdc:https:/openrouter.ai/docs/features/uptime-optimization)
- Always use OpenRouter authentication and API endpoints securely:
  - [Authentication](mdc:https:/openrouter.ai/docs/api-reference/authentication)
  - [List Available Models](mdc:https:/openrouter.ai/docs/api-reference/list-available-models)
  - [Chat Completion](mdc:https:/openrouter.ai/docs/api-reference/chat-completion)
  - [Completion](mdc:https:/openrouter.ai/docs/api-reference/completion)
- Never hardcode API keys or secrets; always use environment variables and secure storage.
- All AI content generation must be server-side only—never expose OpenRouter keys or logic in frontend code.
- Document all AI content generation flows, available models, and integration points in the codebase, README, and `docs/` directory.
- Follow all other project rules for modularity, security, maintainability, and documentation.

## Implementation Requirements
- Set up OpenRouter integration at project initialization, including authentication, model selection, and feature configuration.
- Use structured outputs and tool calling for all content generation tasks where possible.
- Expose a clear, documented API for content generation, with endpoints for product titles, descriptions, SEO metadata, and other needs.
- Log all AI interactions, errors, and model usage for monitoring and debugging.
- Regularly update the list of available free models and their capabilities in the codebase and documentation.
- Reference all relevant OpenRouter docs and endpoints for future agent self-prompting and troubleshooting.

